1.1 Setting Up the Basic Environment

(1) Install Xcode Command Line Tools, which is a foundational dependency for many tools. The command is as follows: xcode-select --install

(2) Install Homebrew, which is a powerful package manager for macOS. Visit https://brew.sh/ to get the installation command.

(3) Install the Conda Environment

Download Miniforge3-MacOSX-arm64.sh to the directory, run the installation script Miniforge3-MacOSX-arm64.sh, activate with conda activate, and activate the configuration with source ~/.zshrc.

2. R Environment Setup:

2.1 Installing R and RStudio

(1) Visit the CRAN mirror website: https://cran.r-project.org/, select the latest .pkg installation package, download and install it.

(2) Visit the RStudio official website: https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/, select "Download RStudio Desktop", download and install it.

2.2 Installing R Packages

(1) Install from CRAN: install.packages("xxx")

(2) Install from Bioconductor.

Modify the mirror:

# Use Tsinghua University's mirror

options(BioC_mirror="https://mirrors.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/bioconductor")

# Install the BiocManager package

if (!require("BiocManager", quietly = TRUE))

    install.packages("BiocManager")

BiocManager::install(version = "3.21") # This version may change; refer to the official website.

# Install R package

BiocManager::install("xxx")
